The paper deals with the problem of testing identity between two distributions, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on high confidence regimes and the use of total variation distance suggest a connection to statistical inference and hypothesis testing, which are also relevant to cs.DS and cs.SI. Finally, the use of black-box amplification and sample complexity analysis suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
